repo.description: The most widely used Python to C compiler
repo.name: cython

body:
Uses the `PyMonitoring` C-API that is being developed for Py3.13.

See https://docs.python.org/3/library/sys.monitoring.html
See https://github.com/python/cpython/issues/111997
See https://github.com/python/cpython/pull/116413

commit.message: Fix macro signatures and add missing dummy macros.
Test runner: Use tag instead of  >version to exclude pstats tests only on Python 3.12, not later.
Trace coroutine resumes as function start in non-monitoring Python.

title: Implement PEP-669 sys.monitoring support
